### 7. Memory and Swap Analysis (`free`)
The `free` command reports system memory parameters. The `-h` flag prints sizes automatically in human-readable formatting (e.g., Gi, Mi).

```bash
free -h
```
**Output:**
```text
              total        used        free      shared  buff/cache   available
Mem:           61Gi        10Gi       7.3Gi       238Mi        44Gi        50Gi
Swap:            0B          0B          0B
```

